         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15/2/92 ¶  ¶ In sending specimens both in flower and in fruit, of Wendlandia basistaminea, ¶  dear Dr Dyer, I like to remark, that Oldenlandia psychotriodes, forward some time ago, consists of Wendlan...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.02.15a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, herbarium, with specimen K760112.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>MS is attached to the herbarium sheet with a specimen identified by M on a standard 'Phytologic Museum of Melbourne' label as <seg style="">'Oldenlandia psychotroides <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>FvM. Mt Bellenden Ker. 1887, W. Sayer'. </seg>The label is annotated in black ink <seg style="">'recd. 9/87'. </seg>The sheet is annotated in pencil: <seg style="">'"Oldenlania psychotroides, x x x constitutes a species of Wendlandia." F v. Mueller in Litt. 21 March 1892'. </seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The date in the note is the date this letter was received at Kew, see n. 3.</p>
               </note>15/2/92</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In sending specimens both in flower and in fruit, of <name key="Wendlandia%20basistaminea">Wendlandia basistaminea</name>,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>Specimen <seg style="">K760113</seg>, identified by M on a standard 'Phytologic Museum of Melbourne' label as '<seg style="">
                        <name key="Wendlandia%20basistaminea">Wendlandia basistaminea</name>, FvM Russell River [Qld] 1892 Steven Johnson'. </seg>The label is annotated 'Recd iii 1892'. </p>
               </note> dear Dr Dyer, I like to remark, that <name key="Oldenlandia%20psychotriodes">Oldenlandia psychotriodes</name>, forward some time ago, consists of Wendlandia, as I have since ascertained. Perhaps you will make the transfer in the herbarium accordingly<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>The letter is date-stamped '21 Mar. 92'. It is annotated in red ink, 'Ackd. 22.3 92 J. B. D. [J. Burtt Davy]' (letter of acknowledgment not found), and in black ink, 'noted JGB <seg style="">[John Gilbert Baker] 21/8/92'. </seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Oldenlandia%20psychotriodes">Oldenlandia psychotriodes</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Wendlandia%20basistaminea">Wendlandia basistaminea</name>
            </p>
